  section#docker
    h3 Intro to Docker &mdash; 28th March
    p Docker is the world’s leading software container platform. Developers use Docker to eliminate “works on my machine” problems when collaborating on code with co-workers. Docker is used to run and manage apps side-by-side in isolated containers. Enterprises use Docker to build agile software delivery pipelines to ship new features faster, more securely and with confidence.
    p During this workshop you’ll learn the basics of Docker and Software Containers including setting up Docker, running your first container, creating a basic web application with Python and Docker, and how to push the Docker Image to DockerHub.
    p: a(href="https://localhost.mlh.io/activities/intro-to-docker/") More info @ https://localhost.mlh.io/activities/intro-to-docker/ &rarr;
    p: a(href="https://www.facebook.com/events/803701049817669/") Facebook Event &rarr;

  section#gitkraken
    h3 Learn Git the Easy Way (using GitKraken) &mdash; 20th Feb
    p Version Control is a vital part of working in a team during software development.
    p In this session you will learn the Git from the basics all the way up to managing multiple branches for each aspect of your software using a with the visual aide of a Git GUI.
    p GitKraken is the most popular Git GUI for Windows / macOS / Linux. GitKraken makes Git commands and processes easy, fast, and intuitive. Enjoy a visually appealing experience that requires fewer interactions, allows for more fluid workflows, and provides total functionality.
    p: a(href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=18w55DPq-0PUQrWppcF-2Yg6m81telAPmOEdebawxMT4") Slides &rarr;
    p: a(href="https://www.facebook.com/events/803701049817669/") Facebook Event &rarr;

  section#pcbuilding
    h3 PC Building &mdash; 6th Feb
    p Come along and build a Desktop PC from scratch!
    p Rob and Guru will take you through the process practically, from selecting components that work together to completing your build, along with an overview of what the part do.
    p Knowing how a computer works could also help you fix your own in the future!
